00:00:00.310 --> 00:00:04.529
ï»¿At the World Economic Forum on East
Asia in Vietnam, we are setting up a Davos

00:00:04.529 --> 00:00:09.880
Debates video corner. Here, participants including
presidents and business leaders will respond

00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:14.240
via video to your questions and ideas on the
region's future.

00:00:14.240 --> 00:00:18.919
The meeting is under the theme: Rethinking
Asia's Leadership Agenda. The key question

00:00:18.919 --> 00:00:25.439
we want to discuss with you is: "How can Asia
lead the world?" The 19th World Economic Forum

00:00:25.439 --> 00:00:30.489
on East Asia will explore the many facets
of the region's rising influence.

00:00:30.489 --> 00:00:35.490
What questions do you have for the leaders
who will gather in Ho Chi Minh City from 6-7

00:00:35.490 --> 00:00:44.290
June 2010? Send your ideas and questions via
video or text to YouTube.com/Davos.

00:00:44.290 --> 00:00:48.190
You can also vote on your favourite contributions
from others.

00:00:48.190 --> 00:00:51.740
The contributions with the highest number
of votes will be put to the leaders at the

00:00:51.740 --> 00:00:57.070
Davos Debates corner giving direct access
to some of the most powerful and influential

00:00:57.070 --> 00:01:01.420
people in the world. The best entries may
also be shown at the meeting.

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:06.570
Tell us what you think.
Go to YouTube.com/Davos to join the conversation.

